Deputy President William Ruto met 146 MPs at his official Karen residence on Wednesday and they issued a statement on the BBI Bill. The full statement issued is below: The journey to consensus Background Reflections on Bomas II recommedations Concerns  by diverse Stakeholders Post-Bomas Changes; Progress Towards Consensus Outstanding Issues and Opportunity to Strike Consensus  “ Let all with one accord In common bond united Build this our nation together”    